SIMPLE: shameless
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shameless
<hw>Shame"less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>scamle⟦aacute⟧s</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Destitute of shame;
wanting modesty; brazen-faced; insensible to disgrace.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Such
<xex>shameless</xex> bards we have.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Shame enough to shame thee, wert thou not
<qex>shameless</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Indicating want of modesty, or sensibility to
disgrace; indecent; <as>as, a <ex>shameless</ex> picture or
poem</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Impudent; unblushing; audacious; immodest;
indecent; indelicate.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Shame"less*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Shame"less*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shame-proof</ent>⟦br⟧
